  "root_text": {
    "sn11.19:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 11.19 ",
    "sn11.19:0.2": "2. Dutiyavagga ",
    "sn11.19:0.3": "Satthāravandanāsutta ",
    "sn11.19:1.1": "Sāvatthiyaṁ jetavane. ",
    "sn11.19:1.2": "“Bhūtapubbaṁ, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo mātaliṁ saṅgāhakaṁ āmantesi: ",
    "sn11.19:1.3": "‘yojehi, samma mātali, sahassayuttaṁ ājaññarathaṁ, uyyānabhūmiṁ gacchāma subhūmiṁ dassanāyā’ti. ",
    "sn11.19:1.4": "‘Evaṁ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkassa devānamindassa paṭissutvā sahassayuttaṁ ājaññarathaṁ yojetvā sakkassa devānamindassa paṭivedesi: ",
    "sn11.19:1.5": "‘yutto kho te, mārisa, sahassayutto ājaññaratho. ",
    "sn11.19:1.6": "Yassadāni kālaṁ maññasī’ti. ",
    "sn11.19:1.7": "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo vejayantapāsādā orohanto añjaliṁ katvā sudaṁ bhagavantaṁ namassati. ",
    "sn11.19:1.8": "Atha kho, bhikkhave, mātali saṅgāhako sakkaṁ devānamindaṁ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
    "sn11.19:2.1": "‘Yañhi devā manussā ca, ",
    "sn11.19:2.2": "taṁ namassanti vāsava; ",
    "sn11.19:2.3": "Atha ko nāma so yakkho, ",
    "sn11.19:2.4": "yaṁ tvaṁ sakka namassasī’ti. ",
    "sn11.19:3.1": "‘Yo idha sammāsambuddho, ",
    "sn11.19:3.2": "asmiṁ loke sadevake; ",
    "sn11.19:3.3": "Anomanāmaṁ satthāraṁ, ",
    "sn11.19:3.4": "taṁ namassāmi mātali. ",
    "sn11.19:4.1": "Yesaṁ rāgo ca doso ca, ",
    "sn11.19:4.2": "avijjā ca virājitā; ",
    "sn11.19:4.3": "Khīṇāsavā arahanto, ",
    "sn11.19:4.4": "te namassāmi mātali. ",
    "sn11.19:5.1": "Ye rāgadosavinayā, ",
    "sn11.19:5.2": "avijjāsamatikkamā; ",
    "sn11.19:5.3": "Sekkhā apacayārāmā, ",
    "sn11.19:5.4": "appamattānusikkhare; ",
    "sn11.19:5.5": "Te namassāmi mātalī’ti. ",
    "sn11.19:6.1": "‘Seṭṭhā hi kira lokasmiṁ, ",
    "sn11.19:6.2": "ye tvaṁ sakka namassasi; ",
    "sn11.19:6.3": "Ahampi te namassāmi, ",
    "sn11.19:6.4": "ye namassasi vāsavā’ti. ",
    "sn11.19:7.1": "Idaṁ vatvāna maghavā, ",
    "sn11.19:7.2": "devarājā sujampati; ",
    "sn11.19:7.3": "Bhagavantaṁ namassitvā, ",
    "sn11.19:7.4": "pamukho rathamāruhī”ti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn11.19:0.1": "Linked Discourses 11.19 ",
    "sn11.19:0.2": "Chapter Two ",
    "sn11.19:0.3": "Who Sakka Worships ",
    "sn11.19:1.1": "Near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove. ",
    "sn11.19:1.2": "“Once upon a time, mendicants, Sakka, lord of gods, addressed his chariot handler Mātali, ",
    "sn11.19:1.3": "‘My dear Mātali, harness the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds. We will go to a park and see the scenery.’ ",
    "sn11.19:1.4": "‘Yes, lord,’ replied Mātali. He harnessed the chariot and informed Sakka, ",
    "sn11.19:1.5": "‘Good fellow, the chariot with its team of a thousand thoroughbreds has been harnessed. ",
    "sn11.19:1.6": "Please go at your convenience.’ ",
    "sn11.19:1.7": "Then Sakka descended from the Palace of Victory, raised his joined palms, and revered the Buddha. ",
    "sn11.19:1.8": "So Mātali the chariot handler addressed Sakka in verse: ",
    "sn11.19:2.1": "‘Gods and men ",
    "sn11.19:2.2": "worship you, Vāsava. ",
    "sn11.19:2.3": "So what’s the name of the spirit ",
    "sn11.19:2.4": "that you worship, Sakka?’ ",
    "sn11.19:3.1": "‘It’s the fully awakened Buddha, ",
    "sn11.19:3.2": "the Teacher of peerless name ",
    "sn11.19:3.3": "in this world with its gods—",
    "sn11.19:3.4": "that’s who I worship, Mātali. ",
    "sn11.19:4.1": "Those in whom greed, hate, and ignorance ",
    "sn11.19:4.2": "have faded away; ",
    "sn11.19:4.3": "the perfected ones with defilements ended—",
    "sn11.19:4.4": "they’re who I worship, Mātali. ",
    "sn11.19:5.1": "The trainees who enjoy reducing suffering, ",
    "sn11.19:5.2": "diligently pursuing the training ",
    "sn11.19:5.3": "for getting rid of greed and hate, ",
    "sn11.19:5.4": "and going past ignorance—",
    "sn11.19:5.5": "they’re who I worship, Mātali.’ ",
    "sn11.19:6.1": "‘Those who you worship ",
    "sn11.19:6.2": "seem to be the best in the world, Sakka. ",
    "sn11.19:6.3": "I too will worship ",
    "sn11.19:6.4": "those who you worship, Sakka.’ ",
    "sn11.19:7.1": "After saying this, Maghavā the chief, ",
    "sn11.19:7.2": "king of gods, Sujā’s husband, ",
    "sn11.19:7.3": "having worshipped the Buddha, ",
    "sn11.19:7.4": "climbed into his chariot.” "
  },
